- 'Shining stars' refers to students who have received at least one B or higher grade in their courses; 
- 'Perfect attendance records' means an attendance percentage of 95% or higher; 
- 'High achievers' are those with a cumulative GPA of 3.5 or higher; 
- 'Academic excellence' in this context means achieving both the GPA and attendance requirements.
